ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If the student is interested in building web applications, I would recommend the course.
The course offers the most current insight into Internet-Scale computing. One of the best/useful courses I took at Yale.
Absolutely! This course draws from many different engineering and theory-oriented disciplines of computer science to convey a subfield of thereof that is new altogether.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course was an excellent opportunity to deepen my knowledge about highly scalable applications. It provided very useful background for the research I work on.
This course complemented my background in networks and network-enabled programming to help understand how the field has evolved to account for newly-developed, parallel computing environments.
